    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks for your solutions (and also for correcting the statement). They make sense to me.</p>\n<p>However, I still wonder whether I can somehow introduce a variable <code>a</code> as a shorthand in such a way that it behaves as if I had written the definition of <code>a</code> at every subsequent appearance. Does that in general require something like <code>have : a = ((max 0 ub) + 5) / 2 := by eq_refl</code>? Or should one always try to reorganize the proof such that a variable is not needed at all (as can be done for this example problem, but perhaps not in all cases)?</p>",
        "id": 507982081,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario F.",
        "timestamp": 1742898166
    },
